SIMPLE: deoxyribose
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: deoxyribose
<hw>deoxyribose</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a pentose
(<chform>C5H10O4</chform>) in which one of the hydroxyl groups of ribose
has been replaced by a hydrogen. In deoxyribonucleic acids, the
deoxyribose is <stype>D-2-deoxyribose</stype>, in which the hydroxyl at
the 2 position of ribose is the one which is replaced by
hydrogen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>deoxyribosenucleic acid</ent>⟦br⟧
